      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/51/8",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ أَعْتَقَ أَمَةً وَ هِيَ حُبْلَى فَاسْتَثْنَى مَا فِي بَطْنِهَا قَالَ \"اَلْأَمَةُ حُرَّةٌ وَ مَا فِي بَطْنِهَا حُرٌّ لِأَنَّ مَا فِي بَطْنِهَا مِنْهَا\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3522 - It is narrated by Al-Sakooni, from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), peace be upon him, regarding a man who freed a pregnant bondwoman but excluded what was in her womb.\nImam (as) said: \"The bondwoman is free, and what is in her womb is also free because what is in her womb is a part of her.\""
        ]
      }
    },
